<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=warrior64&buddyTimeStamp=20050906&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fmillsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fload_buddy_xml.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1193060448&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>Warrior Crunch</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Warrior Crunch lives at <a href='/home/?user=warrior64'>1378 Pond Road</a>, in a lovely, old house that's right on the shore of Lakeview.  He has been enjoying life on the beach since July 17, 2004!<br><br>Any visitor to Warrior Crunch's home could see that he has a very well-stocked trophy cabinet.  A very athletic fellow, he's willing to try any game or sport at least once.  Warrior Crunch has trophies for <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=13">Hop-N-Drop</a>, <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=19">Peabody Park Clean Up</a>, and <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=80">Countdown</a>, which prove that his talents include community awareness and academics, as well as sports.  He's also a half-pipe master who spends hours practicing new tricks on his blue and red skateboard at the half-pipe in <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/peabody_park/">Peabody Park</a>.  Warrior Crunch enjoys fishing too, as a way of chilling out and relaxing, plus he's also won a fishing master trophy.  Warrior Crunch's two favorite sports to play, though, are football and baseball, so he pretty much stays out on the field all year round!  Whether he's starting at quarterback or just sitting in the stands, there's always a good chance of finding Warrior Crunch at a football game.  Without fail, he'll be the one who's cheering the loudest!<br><br>Warrior Crunch also brings his sporty, competitive nature into his everyday life.  One of his favorite places to hang out with friends is at the pool, where he's always challenging them to a friendly race or trying to put together a quick game of water polo.  Warrior Crunch uses his competitive edge at the arcade too, where he's always looking to top his latest high score or battling it out on the newest video game with a friend.  After all, he isn't named Warrior Crunch for nothing! <br><br>Warrior Crunch's spirit of competition is what originally brought him to the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/studio/">Millsberry Recording Studio</a>.  After seeing some of his friends top the charts, he decided that he wanted to challenge himself to see if he could excel at songwriting too.  Sure enough, Warrior Crunch's drive to reach his goal, combined with his love of modern rock, new wave, and pop, led him straight onto the Cinnamon Toast Crunch Top Ten chart!<br><br>In spite of his passion for success, Warrior Crunch has a relaxed side too, and he never lets his competitive nature interfere with making friends.  He likes to keep his friends laughing as much as possible with his great sense of humor.   By putting his comical talents to good use, Warrior Crunch hopes that he can brighten his friends' days when they are feeling a little down. <br><br>Thanks for being a fine citizen, Warrior Crunch, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week.<br></div>
